'''Wollner Building''' is a historic commercial building located at [[Lewistown, Pennsylvania|Lewistown]], [[Mifflin County, Pennsylvania]], on Monument Square across from the [[Mifflin County Courthouse]].  It was built in 1906, and is a three-story, vernacular brick building with a chamfered corner measuring approximately 30 feet by 90 feet.  It sits on a rusticated stone base and has three wood storefronts.  For many years it housed the Lewistown Trust Company.<ref name="arch">{{cite web| url = https://www.dot7.state.pa.us/ce/SelectWelcome.asp| title = "National Historic Landmarks & National Register of Historic Places in Pennsylvania"| publisher = CRGIS: Cultural Resources Geographic Information System| format = Searchable database}} ''Note:'' This includes {{cite web| url = https://www.dot7.state.pa.us/ce_imagery/phmc_scans/H064339_01H.pdf| title = National Register of Historic Places Inventory Nomination Form: Wollner Building| accessdate = 2011-12-29| author = Patrick W. O'Bannon| format = PDF| date= June 1984}}</ref>

It was added to the [[National Register of Historic Places]] in 1984.<ref name="nris"/>

